data.name: Slicer-SegmentGeometry
data.description: Extension to calculate second moment of area and other cross-sectional properties in 3D Slicer

evidence: README mentions binaries/installers: "The official method of obtaining SlicerBiomech is through 3D Slicer's built-in Extensions Manager. To obtain SlicerBiomech, first install the most recent stable release of <a href="https://download.sl"

"This is the repository for the SlicerBiomech extension for 3D Slicer. SlicerBiomech enables the collection and modeling of biomechanical data from 3D specimen data, within the 3D Slicer application."
"Use the 3D Slicer Extensions Manager module to search for SlicerBiomech and install the extension. After restarting 3D Slicer, SlicerBiomech modules will be available to use in the application."
